Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.16,0:00:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte met with Frau Gerlach personally \Nto make a plea: "Please don't marry my dad."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.22,0:00:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,However, even the possibility of that had been ruled out.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.22,0:00:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Deeply shocked, Lotte had fallen ill with a terrible fever.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.13,0:00:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,In the meantime, the photographer \Nfrom the Seebühl Village, Herr Eipeldauer
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.13,0:00:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,decided to send the photo of Lotte and Luise
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.54,0:00:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to Editor-in-Chief Bernau from the Munich Graph magazine \Nas a candidate for the cover photo. {added}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.12,0:00:37.12,Sign,,0,0,100,,{\c&HEAFCF9&\bord0\blur0.8\fs20}Episode 23 \N {\fs45} Sorry, Mom! \N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N {\fs23} \h Translation: Perevodildo | Timings: Sub-RoRo \h
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.64,0:00:41.09,Sign,,0,0,0,,Seebühl Village
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.03,0:00:47.33,Sign,,0,0,0,,Eipeldauer's Photo Studio {写真館}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.80,0:00:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,"To Munich Graph Publishing House."{no clue what's last word, most likelky "... and Company; Messrs; for the attention of ...​"}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.01,0:00:59.45,Default,,0,0,0,,If there's ever a photo good enough, it's this one.  {no clue what he means by "this guy possibly; by some possibility; perhaps, perhaps; maybe; possibly​."; deepl: This guy is going to get a twitch. - maybe he really means "their Editor is going to be startled"}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.33,0:01:19.87,Sign,,0,0,0,,Egern Station
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.91,0:02:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor Strobl had mentioned \Na severe mental shock as the possible reason...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.05,0:02:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise, what in the world had happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.92,0:02:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Just... what?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.22,0:02:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.38,0:03:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Herr Master, have you been up this whole time?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.64,0:03:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,She seems to have settled down a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.43,0:03:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The fever won't subside.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.37,0:03:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Call Doctor Strobl again, Resi.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.18,0:03:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.83,0:03:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is there not a word from Lotte?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.77,0:03:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,There's also this uneasiness in my chest. {I translated it as perturbation (chest-thumping/uneasiness; vague apprehension; premonition) last time but it was in narrator's line and i decided to make narrator sound more old-fashioned/literary, and it's the complete opposite of my vision for Luise}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.92,0:03:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, something happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.31,0:03:49.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyone home, Lotte? {/Earth to Lotte!}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.45,0:03:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.18,0:03:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,What's with that blank look? {absence of mind; fool; blockhead; dunce}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.39,0:03:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Is something troubling you right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.39,0:03:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Not a single itsy-bitsy thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.06,0:04:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.07,0:04:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Not need to rush like that. {maybe she means "calm down now to let the food pass"}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.53,0:04:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.20,0:04:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom, you coming early today?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.60,0:04:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I have one interview planned for today. \NAfter that, will probably have to finish the manuscript.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.41,0:04:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,All in all, it spells "Late" to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.44,0:04:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it. Good luck with your work.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.08,0:04:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's green.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.28,0:04:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm off!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.52,0:04:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Take care!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.60,0:04:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,This would help to bring the fever down, right? {Ihope he means this by "this time, the fever goes down"}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.94,0:04:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Only God knows. {/can't guarantee}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.40,0:04:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.19,0:04:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,With medicine, I can make the fever \Nsubside for an hour or two.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.68,0:04:55.45,Default,,0,0,0,,But I've no sway whatsoever \Nover her mental state. {I hope he means this and not "but I can't do miracles/spiritual healing"}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.07,0:04:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're saying the reason lies in mental plane...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.31,0:05:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything particular comes to your mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.41,0:05:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,A complete blankness...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.35,0:05:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Until now, Luise had been going to school quite cheerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.59,0:05:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Day after day, she was a paragon of joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.86,0:05:17.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Something that could have shocked her...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.83,0:05:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet, at present, \Nshe is traumatized and in an agonizing fever. {lit is "suffering to the point of erupting into fever"}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.47,0:05:28.11,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a serious condition. Can't you really think \Nof any event that could have caused it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.08,0:05:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Consider all the possibilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.95,0:05:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,There was definitely something...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.97,0:05:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And here I was, thinking \NI know my Luise through and through.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.17,0:05:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Resi, what about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.87,0:05:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.70,0:05:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, while I was away, \Nwasn't there anything strange happening to her? {I hope he means this by "changed thing"}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.88,0:06:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything helps, any tiniest detail.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.25,0:06:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't recall anything in connection to this. I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.20,0:06:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.24,0:06:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,What, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.45,0:06:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Just what could be tormenting Luise?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.06,0:06:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.60,0:06:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.23,0:06:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure if it has anything to do with this...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.41,0:06:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything helps. Speak out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.73,0:06:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yesterday morning, \Nwhen the fever didn't strike her yet, {/before she fell ill}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.75,0:06:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,she told me she is going to Cobenzl Boulevard.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.98,0:06:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Cobenzl Boulevard?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.32,0:06:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that all that happened? {unsure what he means}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.25,0:06:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, as I said, \NI don't know if it has anything to do with this...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.16,0:07:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Cobenzl Boulevard?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.76,0:07:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That's where Frau Irene Gerlach's residence is!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.63,0:07:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,But still, why?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.42,0:07:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.56,0:07:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I beg your pardon.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.19,0:07:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Frau, a call from Herr Palfy for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.17,0:07:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Really? Redirect the call here, will you? {link; connection; tie; bond; contact​}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.34,0:07:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Certainly.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.08,0:07:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello? Herr Palfy?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.17,0:07:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Irene listening.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.71,0:07:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm told you had an extremely \Nsuccessful concert last night. {/this time's performance was well-received, it seems}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.41,0:07:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes... Luise appeared on my doorstep out of nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.82,0:07:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... So Luise really did? She went there to see you? \NBut pray, what did she want? {lit: after all, luise, did she visited your house? then, with what business?}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.03,0:08:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,This is something I hoped we'd discuss in person, \Nshould a good occasion arise. {Im about to blow my brains out, I've no fucking clue what she means, deepl has it "I had hoped that we could talk about that once we had a chance." if I replace omotte with motte which is the only way for it to start making sense somehow, even if I still don't see the logistics behind this myself and not 100% sure she doesn't mean "I wanted to discuss that thoroughly once we're all together" or "I thought she would'nt have the guts to tell you about it herself" (esp. when it was "But how did she happen to tell you?"" in the book) or w/e}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.46,0:08:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,For now, pray tell, what did Luise want?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.74,0:08:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure. She came here to tell me, \N"You can't marry Herr Palfy."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.54,0:08:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I asked her for the reason, \Nbut she just kept insisting, "You can't."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.11,0:08:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,She was like a broken record! {persistence; single-mindedness; sticking to one point; focusing on one thing}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.84,0:08:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Pardon my straightforwardness, \Nbut don't you find the very idea appalling? {unreasonable; irrational; outrageous; absurd}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.52,0:08:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, I cut it short \Nand returned in the most unequivocal terms:
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.69,0:08:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,"Calling off my marriage with Herr Palfy \Nis absolutely out of question."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.56,0:08:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The matters of our marriage are not for children to decide. \NBesides, it's settled already. {lit: has no relation/connection to children}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.33,0:08:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello? Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.60,0:08:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Hung up?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.65,0:09:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,What? She went there to tell her "Don't marry?"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.55,0:09:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,My! I had no idea you've gotten \Nthat far with the madam already! {really hope she means this by "the story progressed"}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.87,0:09:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,This pinpoints the cause underlying the fever \Nwith quite the certainty.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.05,0:09:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.75,0:09:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I never realized the extent of your brooding over it. {to think hard; to brood over; to worry too much (about); to torment oneself (with the thought of)}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.65,0:09:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I'm doing it for your own good, \Nthought you need a mother of sorts...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.87,0:09:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, why are you that much opposed to it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.75,0:09:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I was sure you and Frau Irene \Nare on your way to becoming friends. {/getting along}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.08,0:10:02.12,Sign,,0,0,0,,Munich Central Post Office {郵便局}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.35,0:10:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The arithmetic class sure was tough today.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.37,0:10:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.26,0:10:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,My personal view on it is this: \NI don't think it was just this one time alone, rather...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.93,0:10:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's just say, whenever I create, \NI don't set a particular theme for that in my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.62,0:10:56.33,Default,,0,0,0,,What I'm saying may lead you to conclude \Nthere's no uniformity in my works -
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.33,0:11:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,at one moment I'm obsessed with one peculiarity, \Nat the next - blown away with something else. {not sure about what's double sonotoki}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.24,0:11:05.47,Sign,,0,0,0,,But unless you have multiple personalities, \Nenforcing a theme upon yourself will lead you nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.47,0:11:08.18,Sign,,0,0,0,,As for uniformity, it will come by itself, in due course.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.67,0:11:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It's strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.16,0:11:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The letters from Lotte just stopped coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.32,0:11:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Was she somehow rendered unable to send them? {/did something happen, preventing her ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.01,0:11:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,As always, good job.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.57,0:11:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Glad to hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.22,0:11:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The time is ripe to propose more formally.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.28,0:11:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, that's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.86,0:11:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,No reason to delay it - tonight! {move with haste (when you have no doubts); strike while the iron is hot​}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.52,0:11:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.59,0:11:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You're speaking out loud.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.87,0:12:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.27,0:12:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome back, Miss Körner.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.57,0:12:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, the mail had arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.47,0:12:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.04,0:12:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It went well?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.90,0:12:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The interview was a breeze.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.58,0:12:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Manuscript will be ready today.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.10,0:12:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Good, counting on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.24,0:12:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Körner...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.47,0:12:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.08,0:12:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.36,0:12:25.33,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.19,0:12:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.83,0:12:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,There's something I want to say to Lotte and you. {not a single clue what oritte may be, on this place in the sentence I'd expect a place or time like "after work" or "this evening" or "at ori restaurant"; assuming it's 降りて I can usspect it means "if we leave aside our ranks and positions"}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.93,0:12:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,To Lotte and me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.97,0:12:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,My, that sounds like a pleasant talk. {/I wonder if it's a good story}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.68,0:12:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Naturally. I hope, you like it...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.01,0:12:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well. We'll be waiting for you today.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.70,0:12:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Sounds good. But I've some more work to sort out, \Nso I'm probably only coming late in the evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.69,0:12:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, I don't mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.13,0:12:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah? Seebühl Village?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.96,0:13:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That letter... Does it say "Eipeldauer" as a sender{ address}?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.56,0:13:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,This one?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.28,0:13:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,He submitted a photo for a cover candidate.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.16,0:13:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,What about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.07,0:13:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Pretty sure, the summer camp Lotte has been to \Nwas also located in that Seebühl Village.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.98,0:13:22.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Something interesting?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.98,0:13:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Two Lottes in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.72,0:13:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,A photomontage, albeit a masterfully crafted one.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.30,0:13:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if I hadn't known our Lotte, \NI'd probably think those are some genuine twins.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.87,0:13:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Why didn't Lotte tell me about this photo... {hope its naze, then I think the missing part is "why didn't lotte [tell me about] this picture"}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.97,0:13:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.34,0:13:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Why didn't she ever tell me \N she got to meet Luise there?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.43,0:13:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I bet, that photographer \Nnever even considered the possibility,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.55,0:13:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that the mother of his model \Nmight be working right here, in Munich Graph.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.71,0:14:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,That girl...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.48,0:14:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Could it be that she is not even Lotte?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.55,0:14:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Lotte is pretty cute on that photo, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.85,0:14:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Editor...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.55,0:14:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you mind if I borrow this for a moment?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.39,0:14:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, no problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.76,0:14:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't seem to be of much use to us. {/we can't use it anyways}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.75,0:14:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It's yours. {/do what you want to it}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.44,0:14:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... See you tonight, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.12,0:15:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever we do, Young Fraulein \Nis not getting one bit better...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.07,0:16:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.68,0:16:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.21,0:16:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.98,0:16:11.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't get married...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.49,0:16:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, Frau Gerlach! Leave us two alone...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.23,0:16:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.38,0:17:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm home.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.32,0:17:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome back, mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.21,0:17:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't even notice!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.78,0:17:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll get your dinner ready in no time, \Njust need to put the plates away.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.25,0:17:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You said you'll be late today, \Nso I wasn't expecting you now. {/but you're back mighty early}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.06,0:17:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I needed to tend to one urgent matter. {really unsure what's the first word, most likely kyuuyou - urgent business}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.80,0:17:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Urgent matter? What's this about?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.80,0:17:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's about you,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.44,0:17:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.67,0:17:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,About me?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.74,0:17:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it? Do te—
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.83,0:18:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Broke... another one.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.15,0:18:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.06,0:18:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.54,0:18:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.86,0:19:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.75,0:19:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Mommy!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.15,0:19:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.53,0:19:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Mommy...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.40,0:19:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Mommy! Mommy!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.61,0:19:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise, it's you!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.21,0:19:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It's really you, Luise...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.61,0:19:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Mommy!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.45,0:19:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Having found herself in a tight mother's clasp, Luise realizes \N that the astonishment in her heart turns to glee. {lit is "understood/realized" but that's weird thing to say, at such a moment I'd rather expect "she didn't realize as/before she knew it, ..."}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.69,0:19:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,No longer as Lotte, but as Luise.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.97,0:19:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,At the same time, Lotte \Nkeeps crying through her dream, tormented by the fever.
Comment: 0,0:20:20.87,0:20:20.87,Sign,,0,0,0,,{chapter}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.81,0:20:30.34,Sign,,0,0,0,,A miserable romance {可哀想ね　ロマンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.34,0:20:33.80,Sign,,0,0,0,,A tear-jerking nuance {涙誘うニュアンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.80,0:20:37.52,Sign,,0,0,0,,If you turn another page of your memories, {想い出のページめくれば}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.52,0:20:40.43,Sign,,0,0,0,,Here she is - heroine of the past {追憶のヒロイン} {actually, "the heroine of the recollections" but that doesn't have a nice ring to it}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.65,0:20:52.07,Sign,,0,0,0,,I raise my eyes to your face - {あなたの面影　見上げて咲いている}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.07,0:20:55.83,Sign,,0,0,0,,Suddenly, I'm in full bloom {unsure, maybe "it's flourishing"}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.83,0:20:59.37,Sign,,0,0,0,,A sunflower amidst the blizzard - {act. in the middle of winter}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.37,0:21:02.77,Sign,,0,0,0,,that would be me, my dear {真冬のひまわり　それが私なの}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.21,0:21:05.94,Sign,,0,0,0,,Always on the verge of freezing, {凍えるような気持ちでいつも}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.79,0:21:09.34,Sign,,0,0,0,,My feelings are out of control -
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.34,0:21:13.89,Sign,,0,0,0,,Too stiff to even say "Do you still love me?" {「好き?」と尋くこともできず}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.89,0:21:18.04,Sign,,0,0,0,,My lips just keep wavering in this wind! {風に揺れていたわ}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.59,0:21:23.24,Sign,,0,0,0,,A pitiful Romance {いじらしいね　ロマンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.24,0:21:26.65,Sign,,0,0,0,,Something that only happens in dreams - {夢のような出来事}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.65,0:21:30.28,Sign,,0,0,0,,Trying hard to forget, I fell even more in love {忘れるために愛したの}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.28,0:21:33.05,Sign,,0,0,0,,with heroine of the past {追憶のヒロイン}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.10,0:21:37.87,Sign,,0,0,0,,Miracle that I came across now is hugging me tight {めぐりあえた奇跡　そっと抱きしめて}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.87,0:21:41.28,Sign,,0,0,0,,This is the story of my life, my duty is to protect it! {私だけの歴史　守ってゆくわ}
Comment: 0,0:21:44.87,0:21:44.87,Sign,,0,0,0,,{chapter}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.25,0:21:46.75,Sign,,0,0,0,,Next episode preview
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.74,0:21:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, I can finally tell mom a million different things!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.24,0:21:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,How we first met in the summer camp, \Nhow we switched places!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.94,0:21:59.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, about how dad is doing!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.62,0:22:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise, I'm so sorry! \NI would have to apologize to mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.86,0:22:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, something happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.60,0:22:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad will... Dad will end up marrying another woman!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.44,0:22:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time, I and Myself:
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.47,0:22:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Hang on, Lotte!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.71,0:22:15.91,Sign,,0,0,0,,Episode 24 \NHang on, Lotte!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.21,0:22:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Look forward to it! {\i0}
